The user updates his self-description as follows: I now gravitate toward guitar-forward classic rock and AOR — anthem-sized singles, catchy riffs, punchy drums, polished radio-ready production, and bold, singalong vocal deliveries. I enjoy greatest-hits-style sequencing that foregrounds immediate hooks and momentum, and I value energetic, forward-mixed electric arrangements that drive songs. I still appreciate vocal-led, melodic material, clear mastering, self-contained memorable tracks, tasteful orchestral or jazz touches when they support the melody, and occasional relaxed-tempo songs for variety. I dislike subdued, mid-tempo, adult-contemporary albums that prioritize atmosphere over hook, distant or overly restrained vocals, meandering progressive passages without payoff, excessive studio gloss that removes energy, and long tracks that lack immediate melodic focus.

